hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Velocity induced at the vortex by its image vortex of circulation $-\kappa$, located at $r'=R^2/r_v$, is given by the Biot–Savart law for a straight line vortex:
$$
\mathbf{v}_{\text{img}}
=\frac{-\kappa}{2\pi}\,\hat{\mathbf{z}}\times\frac{\mathbf{r}_v-\mathbf{r}'}
{|\mathbf{r}_v-\mathbf{r}'|^2}\,.
$$
On the $x$–axis $\mathbf{r}_v=(r_v,0)$ and $\mathbf{r}'=(R^2/r_v,0)$ so $\mathbf{r}_v-\mathbf{r}'=((r_v-R^2/r_v),0)\equiv(-\Delta,0)$ with $\Delta=(R^2-r_v^2)/r_v$. Thus
$$
\mathbf{v}_{\text{img}}
=\frac{-\kappa}{2\pi}\,\frac{(-\Delta)\,\hat{\mathbf{y}}}{\Delta^2}
=\frac{\kappa}{2\pi}\,\frac{1}{\Delta}\,\hat{\mathbf{y}}
=\frac{\kappa}{2\pi}\,\frac{r_v}{R^2-r_v^2}\,\hat{\boldsymbol\theta}\,.
$$

2. The background solid-body rotation $\mathbf{v}_{bg}=\Omega\,\hat{\mathbf{z}}\times\mathbf{r}$ at $r=r_v$ is
$$
v_{bg}=\Omega\,r_v\,,\quad\text{in the }\hat{\boldsymbol\theta}\text{ direction.}
$$

3. The vortex moves with the sum of these velocities (excluding its self-field), so its angular speed around the axis is
$$
\omega_p=\frac{v_{bg}+v_{\text{img}}}{r_v}
=\frac{\Omega\,r_v+\displaystyle\frac{\kappa\,r_v}{2\pi\,(R^2-r_v^2)}}{r_v}
=\Omega+\frac{\kappa}{2\pi\,(R^2-r_v^2)}\,.
$$
